<br>
Here is a list of the main factions we are going to worry about.<br>
<br>
Freeport Militia (E/W Fp Guards)<br>
Coalition of Tradefolk  (Most Fp vendors, including bankers) <br>
Coalition of Tradefolk Illegall  shows up as<br>
Coalition of Tradefolk Ill  (The rest of the Fp Vendors)<br>
Knights of Truth  (N Fp Paladin Guards)<br>
Ashen Order (Fp Monks(located in wfp))<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm going to assume that you are very kos to everyone. <br>
I will also assume that you want to walk freely in all of fp, including sell, and bank.<br>
<br>
Actual faction adjustments for each quest are located at the bottom of the post.<br>
<br>
1st step is The rogue message quests.  My advise, either pay someone to run it for you, or make a little bard lvl em to 5(for speed songs) and start runnin.  These are in the efp underground area under the bar on the dock.<br>
<br>
If you yourself can run it:<br>
Hail harkin and ask him &quot;What message?&quot;  He'll tell ya where to go, and give you a lore note.<br>
<br>
and <br>
Hail Nestral TGaza and ask here &quot;Where is Janam and Rebby's?&quot; And give you a lore note.<br>
<br>
If you cant run it yourself, only do the Nestral part.<br>
The two guys you are looking for are over by the monk guild in wfp.  One guard roams that area, Guard Inofus i think.   While he is walking past/stopped beside them he will try to take your head, but on the 2 opposite sides of his path he wont, so you *could* run it if you are handy with fd.  My necro did it with a circlet of shadows(trading does cancel it(even though the icon doesn't come off.))<br>
You will get a note for harkin, lore, and Rebby's wiskers(stackable.)<br>
<br>
Basically get a ton of wiskers and turn those in one at a time to Nestral(if you can run it yourself)<br>
<br>
After about 30 or so you will be amiable to the rogues and all the merchants in fp(not including all the guild merchants)<br>
<br>
After about 120 faction adjustments you will probably be dubious to the guards(iksar monk numbers, if you've bottomed out your faction it will probalby be more)<br>
<br>
Once you get threatingly you might, depending on religion, get a wolf form.  It might make you indifferent to fp militia enabling you to do df belt quests.  <br>
<br>
Deathfist Slashed Belt quest.  In the back on the balcony of the fp miltia house  Captain Hazran will take em.  Much easier to get militia faction this way.  Great for getting +dubious. (Problem with this quest is that is also lowers some factions)<br>
<br>
Nfp Faction is alot easier, just stay away from the major guilds.   There is one awesome quest.  Tumpy Tonics for Groflah.  Groflah Steadirt spawns in the Wfp dock bar.  He spawns over by the table by the stairs up.  Give him a alot of em all unstacked.  I gave about 64 and my monk went from scowling to dubious.   He spawns around 8-9pm game time.  If someone is there, you can kill them around 6-7 and he'll spawn.  He was indiffernt to my monk, so I dont' have a clue what faction he is on.  He is only lvl 12 anyway. NOTE. this is the one in wfp, not the merchant in Nfp. (same guy different place.<br>
<br>
The other way to get +Knights of truth is to kill df orcs. Get ready to kill alot of them.  Since they fixed the faction problems you don't have to worry about one bottoming out and you stoping getting faction.  That is also the only way to get +Ashens order faction.  Go to WC and kill the orc camp there.  Over and Over and Over and over.  <br>
